          From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia                            Jump to:     navigation,      search          The 1986 IIHF European U18 Championship' was the nineteenth playing of the IIHF European Junior Championships.    Contents   1 Group A  1.1 First round 1.2 Final round   2 Tournament Awards 3 Group B  3.1 First round 3.2 Final round   4 Group C 5 References    Group A[edit] Played from April 3–9, in Düsseldorf, Ratingen, and Krefeld, West Germany. On the final day of the tournament, the Soviets played to a four all draw with the Swedes, leaving them in fourth place, out of the medals. In the twenty-four years that the Soviets played at the European Juniors (1968 to 1991), this is one and only time they finished out of the medals.[1] First round[edit]  Group 1    Team FIN SWE NOR ROM GF/GA Points   1.  Finland  6:0 13:4 18:1 37:05 6   2.  Sweden 0:6  3:3 23:1 26:10 3   3.  Norway 4:13 3:3  8:5 15:21 3   4.  Romania 1:18 1:23 5:8  07:49 0    Group 2    Team TCH URS FRG SUI GF/GA Points   1.  Czechoslovakia  3:3 9:0 9:3 21:06 5   2.  Soviet Union 3:3  10:1 5:2 18:06 5   3.  West Germany 0:9 1:10  9:2 10:21 2   4.   Switzerland 3:9 2:5 2:9  07:23 0   Final round[edit]  Championship round    Team FIN SWE TCH URS GF/GA Points   1.  Finland  (6:0) 4:4 10:5 20:09 5   2.  Sweden (0:6)  4:3 4:4 08:13 3   3.  Czechoslovakia 4:4 3:4  (3:3) 10:11 2   4.  Soviet Union 5:10 4:4 (3:3)  12:17 2    Placing round    Team FRG SUI NOR ROM GF/GA Points   1.  West Germany  (9:2) 3:2 6:3 18:07 6   2.   Switzerland (2:9)  4:2 7:2 13:13 4   3.  Norway 2:3 2:4  (8:5) 12:12 2   4.  Romania 3:6 2:7 (5:8)  10:21 0   Romania was relegated to Group B for 1987. Tournament Awards[edit]  Top Scorer Tero Toivola (17 points) Top Goalie: Radek Toth Top Defenceman:Kari Harila Top Forward: Morgan Samuelsson  Group B[edit] Played from March 16 to 22, 1986, in Aoste Italy. First round[edit]  Group 1    Team DEN FRA NED ITA GF/Ga Points   1.  Denmark  6:2 6:2 5:3 17:07 6   2.  France 2:6  